# .mailmap — normalize author/committer identity display in git history.
#
# This does NOT rewrite history. It only changes how names/emails are displayed
# by git tools (git shortlog, git log, GitHub contributor graph). The underlying
# commits are untouched.
#
# The repo owner committed under two identities; both are unified below under the
# canonical GitHub-linked identity. Upstream attribution (karpathy) is left as-is
# and intentionally NOT remapped.
#
# Format: Canonical Name <canonical-email> <other-email-to-map>

